erence Handbook: A Reference Handbook |date=2016 |publisher=ABC-CLIO |isbn=978-1-4408-4283-2 |page=227 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=_UzODAAAQBAJ&pg=PA227&dq=1759++measles++north++america#v=onepage&q=1759%20%20measles%20%20north%20%20america&f=false |accessdate=12 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n| [[North America]], [[West Indies]]\n| 1761\n|\n| [[Influenza]]\n|\n|-\n| \n| [[North America]], present-day [[Pittsburgh]] area.\n| 1763\n| \n| [[Smallpox]]\n|<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Ranlet |first1=Philip |title=The British, the Indians, and Smallpox: What Actually Happened at Fort Pitt in 1763? |journal=Pennsylvania History: A Journal of Mid-Atlantic Studies |date=2000 |volume=67 |issue=3 |pages=427\u2013441 |issn=0031-4528|jstor=27774278 }}</ref>\n|-\n| >&nbsp;50,000\n| [[Russian Empire|Russia]]\n| 1770\u20131772\n| [[Russian plague of 1770\u20131772]]\n| [[Plague (disease)|Plague]]\n|\n|-\n|\n| [[Indigenous peoples of the Pacific Northwest Coast|Pacific Northwest natives]]\n| 1770s\n|\n| [[Smallpox]]\n| <ref>Greg Lange,[http://www.historylink.org/essays/output.cfm?file_id=5100 \"Smallpox epidemic ravages Native Americans on the northwest coast of North America in the 1770s\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080526181907/http://www.historylink.org/essays/output.cfm?file_id=5100 |date=2008-05-26 }}, 23 Jan 2003, HistoryLink.org, ''Online Encyclopedia of Washington State History'', accessed 2 Jun 2008</ref>\n|-\n|\n| [[North America]]\n| 1772\n|\n| [[Measles]]\n|\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"025000000\" | >&nbsp;2,000,000\n| [[Iran|Persia]]\n| data-sort-value=\"1772\" | 1772\n| [[1772-1773 Persian Plague|Persian Plague]]\n| [[Plague (disease)|Plague]]\n| <ref name=\"Shahraki\">Shahraki, Abdolrazag Hashemi (2016), [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5037359/ ''Plague in Iran: Its history and current status''].</ref>\n\n|-\n|\n| [[England]]\n| 1775\u20131776\n|\n| [[Influenza]]\n| <ref name=\"Lancet\">{{Cite journal |last=Prichard |firs