hemi (2016), [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5037359/ ''Plague in Iran: Its history and current status''].</ref>\n\n|-\n|\n| [[England]]\n| 1775\u20131776\n|\n| [[Influenza]]\n| <ref name=\"Lancet\">{{Cite journal |last=Prichard |first=Augustin |last2=Fothergill |first2=John |year=1894 |title=Influenza in 1775 |url=https://zenodo.org/record/1663344 |journal=The Lancet |volume=143 |issue=3673 |pages=175\u2013176 |doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(01)66026-4 |access-date=2019-07-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103214437/https://zenodo.org/record/1663344 |archive-date=2020-01-03 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n|\n| [[Spain]]\n| 1778\n| \n| [[Dengue fever]]\n|<ref>{{cite book |last1=Roh\u00e9 |first1=George Henry |last2=Robin |first2=Albert |title=Text-book of Hygiene: A Comprehensive Treatise on the Principles and Practice of Preventive Medicine from an American Standpoint |date=1908 |publisher=Davis |page=[https://archive.org/details/textbookhygiene00robigoog/page/n450 428] |url=https://archive.org/details/textbookhygiene00robigoog |quote=spain 1788 dengue fever. |accessdate=12 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n| [[Plains Indians]]\n| 1780\u20131782\n| [[North American smallpox epidemic]]\n| [[Smallpox]]\n| <ref>{{Cite journal |last=Houston |first=C. S. |last2=Houston |first2=S. |year=2000 |title=The first smallpox epidemic on the Canadian Plains: In the fur-traders' words |journal=The Canadian Journal of Infectious Diseases |volume=11 |issue=2 |pages=112\u20135 |doi=10.1155/2000/782978 |pmc=2094753 |pmid=18159275}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n| [[Pueblo Indians]]\n| 1788\n|\n| [[Smallpox]]\n|<ref>{{cite book |last1=Waldman |first1=Carl |last2=Braun |first2=Molly |title=Atlas of the North American Indian |date=2009 |publisher=Infobase Publishing |isbn=978-1-4381-2671-5 |page=295 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=P2HKD9PgC6wC&pg=PA295&dq=pueblo+indian+1788+smallpox#v=onepage&q=pueblo%20indian%201788%20smallpox&f=false |accessdate=12 February 2020 |languag